fields.description:
Trying to build pyarrow on CentOS or Fedora fails to load libarrow.so. The build does not use conda, rather is similar to the OSX build instructions. 

 A dockerfile is available here:

https://github.com/ryanmackenziewhite/dockers/blob/master/centos7-py36-arrowbuild/Dockerfile
{code:java}
// ImportError while loading conftest '/work/repos/arrow/python/pyarrow/tests/conftest.py'.
pyarrow/__init__.py:54: in <module>
from pyarrow.lib import cpu_count, set_cpu_count
E ImportError: libarrow.so.12: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory
{code}

comments.body:
Great, thanks [~wesmckinn] ... I figured I overlooked something trivial.

Missing the hypothesis module as well.
{code:java}
ImportError while loading conftest '/work/repos/arrow/python/pyarrow/tests/conftest.py'.
pyarrow/tests/conftest.py:20: in <module>
import hypothesis as h
E ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'hypothesis'
{code}
Adding the hypothesis package during the pip install fixes everything. 
{code:java}
pip install six numpy pandas cython pytest hypothesis
{code}

Update virtualenv pip install instructions to include hypothesis

[http://arrow.apache.org/docs/python/development.html#developing-on-linux-and-macos]
{code:java}
virtualenv pyarrow
source ./pyarrow/bin/activate
pip install six numpy pandas cython pytest hypothesis{code}
